table-1478-761.caption: Season 3, 1969-1970
data: Sister Bertrille takes charge of the convent's softball team.
Sister Bertrille lets fame go to her head after a television executive takes notice of her talents.
Sister Bertrille pairs a shy priest up with Carlos' comedy-writer friend before a sermon.
Sister Bertrille plays matchmaker for an estranged couple so they can be a family for their baby.
A orphan boy decides that he want Carlos to be his father, so he places an ad in the newspaper so Carlos can have a bride and a mother.
Sister Bertrille is caught in the middle of a standoff between angry picketers and the company's management.
A tabloid reporter is determined to get a scoop on reports of a flying nun, which could mean trouble for both the convent and Sister Bertrille.
The nuns welcome a stranded man to stay with them, unaware that he is a millionaire.
A donkey shakes up things in more ways than one at the casino.
Sister Bertrille is grounded due to the wardrobe changes for the nuns that includes wingless bonnets.
The nuns find another chance to raise money by taking advantage of the Mother General's past as a silent film star
Sister Bertrille decides to spend time in jail to teach a boy the value of what happens when a person breaks the law.
Carlos decides to go for a conservative look in order to impress Sister Bertrille's visiting cousin from Boston.
Sister Bertrille becomes an advice columnist for a newspaper, and her answers brings nothing but trouble for Carlos.
Sister Bertrille's sister stay at the convent takes an unlikely twist involving an expectant mother and posing as a pianist.
A orphan becomes a pool shark after Carlos donates a pool table to the convent.
Sister Bertrille casts Carlos' cousin in a play.
A trouble-making orphan changes his ways in order to be adopted.
Sister Bertrille is caught in a bizarre triangle between a plumber and a dog.
Did Sister Bertrille sleep while flying? Carlos thinks he saw Sister Bertrille fly while asleep.
The Korean orphan that Carlos adopted shows up to finally meet Carlos... as a 19-year-old beauty.
A hidden camera commercial for a detergent turns up an unlikely star: Sister Bertrille!
Sister Bertrille helps a bullfighter when she volunteers to tutor him. But his manager is determined to spear him back to the ring after learning that he is staying at the convent.
A witness in a car mishap decides to protect Sister Bertrille from being accused, only to have a music duo end up taking the blame.
When an abandoned baby is left on the doorstep of the covenant's secretary, Sister Bertrille takes it upon herself to find out who was responsible for doing it by conducting her own investigation.
Sister Bertrille helps a bridegroom make it down the aisle on the fifth try by convincing him that he is not dying.

table-1478-759.caption: Season 1, 1967-1968
data: The arrival of Sister Bertille to Puerto Rico to start her life as a novice at the Convent San Tanco takes off when she discovers that she can fly. This discovery also causes alarm for not only Sister Jacqueline, but for the Mother Superior after she returns from a meeting abroad. NOTE: one-hour series premiere
After Casino owner Carlos sees Sister Bertille fly, he begins a change of heart and lifestyle that prompts Bertille to intervene.
Sister Bertille deals with a greedy car dealer as she attempts to buy a new station wagon for the convent
Sister Bertille and Carlos attempt to restore an ocean-damaged church bell that once rang at the convent
The nuns believe that Sister Bertrille might be dying after hearing rumors that she came in contact with a poisoned plant
"Polly Wants a Crack in the Head"
Sisters Bertrille and Jacqueline try to hide a parrot in the convent.
"Ah Love, Could You and I Conspire"
The girlfriend of a hit man hides out at the convent and ends up making fast friends with the nuns.
The nuns attempt to sell home made wine, only to learn that when it comes to the business side, the glass is half full.
A pelican falls for Sister Bertrille after she rescues the injured bird.
While the Mother Superior is away, Sister Bertrille, in an attempt to retrieve an item, lands by accident on an island that is occupied by gamblers.
A boy with a knack for telling lies sees Sister Bertrille fly, but when he tells other, they think he is making the story up.
Sister Bertrille and Jaqueline play peacemaker for a nearby feuding town.
"If You Want To Fly, Keep Your Coronet Dry"
Two kids wants to learn how to fly... just like their mentor, Sister Bertrille.
Sister Bertrille attempts to make it "snow" at the convent.
A young boy believes that Sister Bertrille is a reincarnation of his late mother, who looks like the Sister. NOTE: No laugh track.
Sister Bertrille is tricked into going fishing with Sister Sixto's uncle.
Carlos transfers the ownership of the casino to the nuns to keep it out of the hands of gangsters without their knowledge.
Carlos falls for Sister Bertrille's sister.
Sister Bertrille becomes a gambler's good luck charm.
Sister Bertrille helps a sailor who is attempting to sail from San Juan to Miami in a tiny boat.
Sister Bertrille helps an illiterate learn to read and write.
Sister Bertrille inherits a boxer from her late uncle, who leaves no punches.
Carlos is called up for service and is divided between his lifestyle and military duty.
"May the Wind Be Always at Your Back"
A teenage girl has a crush on Carlos.
A orphan at the convent befriends a kleptomaniac canine with a habit of picking pockets.

table-1478-760.caption: Season 2, 1968-1969
data: A rock band offer their services to perform at the convent.
The Police officer suspects that the nuns are running a crooked bazaar after $25 is reported missing, so he hires a gardener to spy on the convent.
The nuns help a gambler make money for his wedding.
The nuns pretend to have the convent condemned so they can convince Carlos not to relocate his casino.
A actress wants to become a nun after hiding out at the convent.
The nuns receive an organ that shatters glass.
After Sister Bertrille rescues a pair of hawk eggs, she is mistaken for a UFO by visiting tourists; Carlos tries to hide from a woman who wants to marry him.
Sister Bertrille is left alone with a fugitive bank robber and a sick boy at the convent while everyone else is at an event.
The nuns end up helping a politician caught up in a case of mistaken identity.
When Sister Bertrille is accused of stealing money from parking meters, she sets out to find the real culprits.
Sister Bertrille tries to stay grounded during an attempt to be picked to accompany the Mother Superior to a ceremony in Chicago.
Sister Bertrille, along with her sister and fiancee, convinces Carlos' grandmother that Carlos is a happily married man.

When the nuns learn that the owner will not renew its 99-year-old lease, they come up with a solution by inviting the its only living relative (the current owner) to stay at the convent. But his arrival has the nuns shocked at who they are dealing with.
Sister Bertrille helps an aging magician regain his spirit in time for a charity show and to reconnect with his nephew.
Carlos invites the nuns to use the casino for an event. But when a couple decides to rob the place with the female partner posing as a nun, suspicions fall on Sister Bertrille's uncle.
Sister Bertrille must find a way to clear her uncle's name and the convent's reputation when she seeks out the real culprits.

When a toy salesman runs into ex-girlfriend Elsie and later discover that she is now Sister Bertrille, he starts to blame himself for breaking off their eight-month relationship and pushed her to be a nun.
Sister Bertrille is accused of stealing after a monkey with a habit of taking things arrives at the convent.
Sister Bertrille helps a brokenhearted cow by using Carlo's yacht to sail the bovine to St. Thomas.
Carlos gets help from a priest in preparing his taxes.
The Police Chief is hoping the nuns remember his birthday.
The nuns go into the bakery business.
Carlos' cousin comes up a business venture that backfires.
A offended comment results in Carlos' large family members moving in with him.
A poor farmer sees Sister Bertrille as his lottery ticket's blessing.

table-1478-780.caption: Known ATA S.M.A.R.T. attributes
data: (Vendor specific raw value.) Stores data related to the rate of hardware read errors that occurred when reading data from a disk surface. The raw value has different structure for different vendors and is often not meaningful as a decimal number.
Overall (general) throughput performance of a hard disk drive. If the value of this attribute is decreasing there is a high probability that there is a problem with the disk.
Average time of spindle spin up (from zero RPM to fully operational [millisecs]).

A tally of spindle start/stop cycles. The spindle turns on, and hence the count is increased, both when the hard disk is turned on after having before been turned entirely off (disconnected from power source) and when the hard disk returns from having previously been put to sleep mode.
Margin of a channel while reading data. The function of this attribute is not specified.

(Vendor specific raw value.) Rate of seek errors of the magnetic heads. If there is a partial failure in the mechanical positioning system, then seek errors will arise. Such a failure may be due to numerous factors, such as damage to a servo, or thermal widening of the hard disk. The raw value has different structure for different vendors and is often not meaningful as a decimal number.
Average performance of seek operations of the magnetic heads. If this attribute is decreasing, it is a sign of problems in the mechanical subsystem.

Count of hours in power-on state. The raw value of this attribute shows total count of hours (or minutes, or seconds, depending on manufacturer) in power-on state. . On some pre-2005 drives, this raw value may advance erratically and/or "wrap around" (reset to zero periodically).

Count of retry of spin start attempts. This attribute stores a total count of the spin start attempts to reach the fully operational speed (under the condition that the first attempt was unsuccessful). An increase of this attribute value is a sign of problems in the hard disk mechanical subsystem.
Recalibration Retries or Calibration Retry Count

This attribute indicates the count that recalibration was requested (under the condition that the first attempt was unsuccessful). An increase of this attribute value is a sign of problems in the hard disk mechanical subsystem.
This attribute indicates the count of full hard disk power on/off cycles.
Uncorrected read errors reported to the operating system.
"Pre-Fail" Attribute used at least in HP devices.
Program Fail Count Total or Non-4K Aligned Access Count

Total number of Flash program operation failures since the drive was deployed. Number of user data accesses (both reads and writes) where LBAs are not 4 KiB aligned (LBA % 8 != 0) or where size is not modulus 4 KiB (block count != 8), assuming logical block size (LBS) = 512 B
SATA Downshift Error Count or Runtime Bad Block
Western Digital and Samsung attribute. (or) Seagate.
The count of errors that could not be recovered using hardware ECC (see attribute 195).

The count of aborted operations due to HDD timeout. Normally this attribute value should be equal to zero and if the value is far above zero, then most likely there will be some serious problems with power supply or an oxidized data cable.

HDD producers implement a Fly Height Monitor that attempts to provide additional protections for write operations by detecting when a recording head is flying outside its normal operating range. If an unsafe fly height condition is encountered, the write process is stopped, and the information is rewritten or reallocated to a safe region of the hard drive. This attribute indicates the count of these errors detected over the lifetime of the drive. This feature is implemented in most modern Seagate drives and some of Western Digital’s drives, beginning with the WD Enterprise WDE18300 and WDE9180 Ultra2 SCSI hard drives, and will be included on all future WD Enterprise products.
Airflow Temperature (WDC) resp. Airflow Temperature Celsius (HP)
Airflow temperature on Western Digital HDs (Same as temp. [C2], but current value is 50 less for some models. Marked as obsolete.)
Value is equal to (100−temp. °C), allowing manufacturer to set a minimum threshold which corresponds to a maximum temperature.
The count of errors resulting from externally induced shock & vibration.
Power-off Retract Count or Emergency Retract Cycle Count (Fujitsu)
Load Cycle Count or Load/Unload Cycle Count (Fujitsu)

Count of load/unload cycles into head landing zone position. The typical lifetime rating for laptop (2.5-in) hard drives is 300,000 to 600,000 load cycles. Some laptop drives are programmed to unload the heads whenever there has not been any activity for about five seconds. Many Linux installations write to the file system a few times a minute in the background. As a result, there may be 100 or more load cycles per hour, and the load cycle rating may be exceeded in less than a year.
(Vendor specific raw value.) The raw value has different structure for different vendors and is often not meaningful as a decimal number.

Count of remap operations. The raw value of this attribute shows the total count of attempts to transfer data from reallocated sectors to a spare area. Both successful & unsuccessful attempts are counted.

Count of "unstable" sectors (waiting to be remapped, because of unrecoverable read errors). If an unstable sector is subsequently read successfully, this value is decreased and the sector is not remapped. Read errors on a sector will not remap the sector immediately (since the correct value cannot be read and so the value to remap is not known, and also it might become readable later); instead, the drive firmware remembers that the sector needs to be remapped, and will remap it the next time it's written. However some drives will not immediately remap such sectors when written; instead the drive will first attempt to write to the problem sector and if the write operation is successful then the sector will be marked good (in this case, the "Reallocation Event Count" (0xC4) will not be increased). This is a serious shortcoming, for if such a drive contains marginal sectors that consistently fail only after some time has passed following a successful write operation, then the drive will never remap these problem sectors.
Uncorrectable Sector Count or Offline Uncorrectable or Off-Line Scan Uncorrectable Sector Count
The total count of uncorrectable errors when reading/writing a sector. A rise in the value of this attribute indicates defects of the disk surface and/or problems in the mechanical subsystem.
The count of errors in data transfer via the interface cable as determined by ICRC (Interface Cyclic Redundancy Check).
The count of errors found when writing a sector. The higher the value, the worse the disk's mechanical condition is.
The total count of errors when writing a sector.
Soft Read Error Rate or TA Counter Detected
Data Address Mark errors or TA Counter Increased
The number of errors caused by incorrect checksum during the error correction.
Count of errors due to high temperature.
Count of buzz routines needed to spin up the drive due to insufficient power.
Drive’s seek performance during its internal tests.
(found in a Maxtor 6B200M0 200GB and Maxtor 2R015H1 15GB disks)
Distance the disk has shifted relative to the spindle (usually due to shock or temperature). Unit of measure is unknown.
The count of errors resulting from externally induced shock & vibration.
Current state of drive operation based upon the Life Curve
Indicates the approximate SSD life left, in terms of program/erase cycles or Flash blocks currently available for use.
Number of physical erase cycles completed on the drive as a percentage of the maximum physical erase cycles the drive is designed to endure
Intel SSD reports the number of available reserved space as a percentage of reserved space in a brand new SSD.
Number of hours elapsed in the power-on state.
Intel SSD reports a normalized value of 100 (when the SSD is new) and declines to a minimum value of 1. It decreases while the NAND erase cycles increase from 0 to the maximum-rated cycles.
Average erase count AND Maximum Erase Count
Decoded as: byte 0-1-2 = average erase count (big endian) and byte 3-4-5 = max erase count (big endian)
Good Block Count AND System(Free) Block Count
decoded as: byte 0-1-2 = good block count (big endian) and byte 3-4 = system(free) block count.
Count of times the link is reset during a data transfer.
Total count of LBAs read. Some S.M.A.R.T. utilities will report a negative number for the raw value since in reality it has 48 bits rather than 32.
Count of errors while reading from a disk

table-1478-455.caption: Air-hardening types
data: A common general purpose tool steel; it is the most commonly used variety of air-hardening steel. It is commonly used for blanking and forming punches, trimming dies, thread rolling dies, and injection molding dies.

This type of tool steel air-hardens at a relatively low temperature (approximately the same temperature as oil-hardening types) and is dimensionally stable. Therefore it is commonly used for dies, forming tools, and gauges that do not require extreme wear resistance but do need high stability.
